ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. Made an effort to get your words right
2. Checked that you were coming across well
3. Deliberately avoided eye contact
4. Tried to picture how you appeared to your partner
5. Rehearsed what you were going to say before speaking
6. Censored what you were going to say
7. Avoided talking about yourself
8. Deliberately asked lots of questions
9. Avoided pauses in your speech
10. Hid or covered your face
11. Tried to think about other things
12. Deliberately talked a lot
13. Tried not to attract attention to yourself
14. Tried to keep tight control of your behavior
15. Tried to appear distant
16. Tried to conceal your anxiety
17. Frequently smiled or nodded your head
18. Acted very agreeable
19. Avoided expressing your opinion
20. Said little or nothing (talked as little as possible)
21. Talked about "safe" or neutral topics
22. Had a pre-determined list of things to talk about
23. Blank out or switch off mentally
24. Try to control shaking
25. Try to say something witty or entertaining
26. Speak very quietly or softly
Safety Behaviors Questionnaire Total Score
